TY  - JOUR
AU  - Faure-Grimaud, Antoine
T1  - Using Stock Price Information to Regulate Firms
PY  - 2002
Y1  - 2002/01/01
DO  - 10.1111/1467-937X.00202
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 69
IS  - 1
SP  - 169
EP  - 190
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper examines the role of the information contained in stock prices in the regulation of privatized firms. Stock prices contain noisy but unbiased information about firm's future prospects that regulators can use to decide on some regulatory policies. The main argument developed is that the observation of stock price movements reduces the incentives of regulators to develop their own monitoring technologies and can allow them to commit to relatively lighthanded regulations. This protects firm's investments in cost reduction activities and can increase ex ante welfare.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-937X.00202
ER  - 



